<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030466>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Entomobrya, habitus of some species.A, E. multisetis sp. nov.; B–C, E. kremenitsai sp. nov.; D–F, E. hirsutothorax sp. nov. (bar 0.25mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5030466/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030470>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Entomobrya multisetis sp. nov. A, head macrochaetotaxy; B, AntIV tip, showing the apical vesicle, and the bifurcate pin chaeta; C, distal area of AntIII showing the sensory organ; D, distal area of AntII showing three special sensilla; E, labral papillae; F, claw and empodium; G, Th II–III dorsal macrochaetotaxy; H, AbdI–III dorsal macrochaetotaxy. The drawing is schematic, except for AbdI in wich the Mc are drawed with its actual form and proportional to size; I, AbdIV dorsal macrochaetotaxy (scale bars: A, G–I, 0.1mm; B and E, 0.01mm; C–D, 0.025mm; F, 0.025mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5030470/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

